    <weatherForecast/>
    <avalancheActivity>
      <highlights>Gliding avalanches can also be released in the morning. Slight increase in avalanche danger as a consequence of warming during the day.</highlights>
      <comment>In particular on cut and grassy slopes more small and medium-sized gliding avalanches are possible, in particular above approximately 1600 m. &lt;br/> Caution is to be exercised in areas with glide cracks. &lt;br/> &lt;br/> The weather conditions will cause a slight rise in the danger of moist avalanches as the day progresses. &lt;br/> Especially above approximately 2200 m: Weak layers in the old snowpack can still be released in some place by winter sport participants. &lt;br/> &lt;br/> In the morning, There is a danger of falling on the hard snow surface.</comment>
    </avalancheActivity>
    <snowpackStructure>
      <comment>Towards its surface, the snowpack is hard and its surface has a melt-freeze crust that is strong in many cases. &lt;br/> Sunshine and high temperatures will give rise from early morning to softening of the snowpack especially on sunny slopes, in the event of an overcast night in particular. &lt;br/> &lt;br/> Intermediate and high altitudes: Weak layers exist in the snowpack especially on west, north and northeast facing slopes. &lt;br/> &lt;br/> In particular in the vicinity of peaks snow depths vary greatly, depending on the infuence of the wind. &lt;br/></comment>
    </snowpackStructure>
    <travelAdvisory/>
    <tendency>
      <tendencyType>steady</tendencyType>
      <validTime>
        <startTime>2026-03-07T23:00:00Z</startTime>
